Four verification points. None are optional. Full playbook: `.claude/skills/iterative-azure-deploy/SKILL.md`. Known error fixes: `.claude/skills/iterative-azure-deploy/references/gotchas.md`.

## 1. Local build + test

```powershell
# Kill orphan processes first — stale dotnet run holds DLL locks
Get-Process EduMap.Api -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Stop-Process -Force
dotnet build
dotnet test --no-build
```

All tests must pass. Never disable a test to unblock a push.

## 2. Smoke test

```powershell
dotnet run --project src/EduMap.Api --no-build &
Start-Sleep 3
curl -s http://localhost:5029/health
curl -s http://localhost:5029/api/countries/RS | python -X utf8 -m json.tool | Select-Object -First 15
Get-Process EduMap.Api | Stop-Process -Force
```

## 3. Commit (read log tone first)

```powershell
git log --oneline -8   # match the existing style before writing
git add src/... tests/...   # explicit files — never git add -A
git commit -m @'
Imperative subject line under 72 chars

Why this change was made. What the user/kid would see before vs after.
What specifically changed and where (file paths are fine).

Requires: <new env var or Azure resource, or omit this line>
'@
git push
```

No emojis. No `Co-Authored-By`. Never `--amend` without explicit permission. Never `--force` push.

## 4. Watch CI/CD (no `gh` CLI — use curl)

```bash
REPO="dmiljkoviclevi9/EduMap"
SHA=$(git rev-parse HEAD | cut -c1-7)
sleep 6

for i in {1..30}; do
  status=$(curl -s "https://api.github.com/repos/$REPO/actions/runs?per_page=3" \
    | python -X utf8 -c "
import sys,json
for r in json.load(sys.stdin).get('workflow_runs',[]):
  if r['head_sha'].startswith('$SHA'):
    print(f\"id={r['id']} status={r['status']} conclusion={r['conclusion']}\"); break
else: print('not yet')
")
  echo "  $i: $status"
  case "$status" in *"status=completed"*) break ;; esac
  sleep 8
done
```

## 5. Verify live site

```powershell
curl -s -w "`nHTTP %{http_code}, %{time_total}s`n" `
  https://edumap-miljkovici.azurewebsites.net/health
# F1 Free cold start = 25-30s. Normal. Don't try to fix it.
```

Hit an endpoint relevant to your specific change. Confirm the response reflects the new data.
